& [ShaliachSelfNegotiationRecordDesign] is the design contract for deterministic Shaliach self-negotiation scaffolding
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-30T09:22:00Z
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [shaliach_module] src/negotiated_agent/shaliach.py

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is deterministic_scaffold_not_live_internal_deliberation
  + [primary_goal] is represent Shaliach higher/lower reasoning refinement before live local model serving is available
  + [non_goal] is claiming live multi-model Shaliach self-negotiation
  + [non_goal] is replacing Shaliach findings or response coordination
  + [non_goal] is making every protocol event expensive
  + [non_goal] is hiding uncertainty behind ceremonial agreement

& [SelfNegotiationInputs] is the minimum evidence required
  + [field] is negotiation_id
  + [field] is subject_ref
  + [field] is intention_statement
  + [field] is purpose_statement
  + [field] is context_boundary
  + [field] is perspective_set
  + [field] is proposed_response_set
  + [field] is resolved_intention
  + [field] is unresolved_tension_set
  + [authority_boundary] is scoped_intention_refinement_not_global_truth
  = must: preserve multiple perspectives even when they agree
  = must: record unresolved tensions rather than deleting them
  = must: state what the negotiation is allowed to influence

& [PerspectiveSet] is the deterministic pre-live perspective roster
  + [perspective] is legal_counsel
  + [perspective] is protocol_officer
  + [perspective] is failure_advocate
  + [perspective] is purpose_guardian
  + [authority_boundary] is deterministic_roles_not_separate_models
  = must: keep perspective labels distinct from the seven-faculty Observer naming
  = must: allow later live model routes to replace or enrich deterministic role text

& [ResolutionPolicy] is how the record should settle a response
  + [status] is resolved_when_no_blocking_tensions
  + [status] is rework_required_when_protocol_or_failure_tension_blocks
  + [status] is advisory_when_tension_is_nonblocking
  + [authority_boundary] is resolution_policy_not_manager_approval
  = must: produce a resolved_intention string
  = must: preserve blocking and advisory tensions separately
  = must: not advance frontiers or apply files

& [ProofExpectations] is the minimum implementation proof for this design
  + [test_case] is record serializes perspectives proposed responses resolved intention and tensions
  + [test_case] is status is rework_required when blocking tensions exist
  + [test_case] is status is advisory when only advisory tensions exist
  + [test_case] is authority boundary states deterministic scaffold not live internal deliberation
  + [test_case] is record can be referenced by existing Shaliach finding or response coordination later

& [ImplementationOrder] is the safe next split
  + [slice_1] is add ShaliachSelfNegotiationRecord and perspective/tension records
  + [slice_2] is add deterministic builder from subject intention purpose and optional tensions
  + [slice_3] is connect record refs into Shaliach findings only after record semantics are tested
